On March 20, 2015, President Barack Obama sent a message to Congress regarding the fiscal year 2015 budget and financial plan for the District of Columbia. The message was in accordance with his constitutional authority and section 446 of the District of Columbia Self-Government and Governmental Reorganization Act. The President stated that the transmission of the budget and financial plan does not indicate his endorsement of the D.C. government's requests. The proposed budget for FY 2015 reflects the main programmatic goals of the Mayor and the Council of the District of Columbia, with total estimated revenues and expenditures of $12.6 billion.